1)  Hook Raspberry pi to power, monitor, keyboard and mouse
2)  Login into the raspberry pi
3)  connect the raspberry pi to wifi
4)  get the ip address ifconfig
            https://www.raspberrypistarterkits.com/how-to/find-raspberry-pi-ip-address/
            
6)  download & install putty on your laptop   
            https://the.earth.li/~sgtatham/putty/latest/w64/putty-64bit-0.76-installer.msi
7)  start putty, in the hostname / ip address enter in the ip aquired in step2
8)  login to raspberry PI
